title: For Sale:  For Sale: Colt 1873 SAA .41 Long Colt Engraved Nickel & Gold Ivory Grips
postcontent:
Impressive Engraved Colt M1873 Single Action Army, Nickel & Gold Plated with Mammoth Ivory Grips, .41 Long Colt, mfg. 1905/1906 with 4 3/4" barrel. A fantastic looking gun that would benefit from further research. We have not lettered the gun, but the engraving is early Colt style, and certainly Colt quality. At bare minimum, this gun was embellished at the period by a master engraver. Of course if the gun were to come back as having any of this work done by Colt, it's value will be substantial. The gun features full scroll coverage engraving, with approx. 80% of a period re-nickel finish. The cylinder, hammer, backstrap, triggerguard, trigger, ejector housing, and screws retain approx. 80% period Gold finish, with minor flaking due to age. Interestingly, the triggerguard and backstrap serial numbers do not match the frame, however they are relatively close in numbers and the work was all done at the same time. Again, a factory letter may help explain things. The grips look to be rare Mommoth Ivory, as opposed to African Elephant Ivory. They have much more of a marbled grain, and exhibit a deep, mellow patina. They are smooth with no chips or cracks. They fit the gun ok along the triggerguard and butt, but are a little low along the backstrap. Clear markings throughout, including the correct two-line barrel address and patent dates. The "41 COLT" marking on the barrel however is very faint. The action works very well and is strong. The bore has fair rifling, with notable blackpowder frosting, especially toward the breech. Overall this is a perfect representation of a classic, highly embellished Peacemaker, and further research may yield some very interesting and valuable information. FFL or C&R required.

Buyer pays actual shipping costs of $35.
